So far, the WIV1 represents the most closely related ancestor of SARS-CoV in bats, which shares a 95% nucleotide sequence homology.
Despite the high homology between these two viruses, in general, it is believed that WIV1 is not the immediate parenting virus of SARS-CoV and that bats are not the immediate reserve guest of SARS-CoV.
According to phylogenetic analysis, the MERS-CoV is classified in the same group as the bat CoV-HKU4 and the bat CoV-HKU5.
