On 11 February 2020, the test was registered by the Federal Medical Surveillance Service. On 12 March 2020, Mayo Clinic was reported to have developed a test to detect the infection by COVID-19. On 13 March 2020, Roche Diagnostics received the approval of the FDA for a test that could be carried out within 3.5 hours in large volumes, allowing a machine to perform approximately 4128 tests in a 24-hour period.
